MacroOracle::requestMacro
├── when the dataKey is not in the catalog
│   └── it should revert with UnknownKey.
└── when the dataKey is in the catalog
    ├── given the endpoint kind is Uint
    │   └── it should send a fetchUint payload over PROXY_BASE+proxyPath, selector "value", decimals 0.
    ├── given the endpoint kind is Int
    │   └── it should send a fetchInt payload over PROXY_BASE+proxyPath, selector "value", decimals 0.
    ├── it should map requestId -> dataKey and mark the request pending.
    └── it should emit MacroRequested.

MacroOracle::onResult
├── given Failed/TimedOut status or empty responses
│   └── it should emit MacroFailed and store nothing.
├── given a non-32-byte result
│   └── it should emit MacroFailed and not revert the callback.
├── given Success on a Uint endpoint
│   └── it should store scaledValue = decoded uint (>int256.max -> MacroFailed, no wrap) + emit MacroReceived.
└── given Success on an Int endpoint
    └── it should store the signed scaledValue (negatives preserved) + emit MacroReceived.

# Agent-call semantics (proven for fetchUint 2026-06-01): selector "value" (no dot), decimals 0
# (proxy pre-scales). Endpoint.decimals is interpretation metadata, NOT passed to the agent.
# observedAt stays 0 (agent fetches only "value", not the proxy "ts"). fetchInt path is
# structurally analogous to fetchUint but not yet live-verified on-chain.
